  "body": "## Issue\r\n\r\nRunning a migration on rinkeby fails unless you skip dry run because it appears that ganache is attempting to hard code chain id 1.  The fact that this was resolved [here](https://github.com/trufflesuite/ganache/pull/532) makes me wonder if it's a versioning issue (though the newest stable release of ganache is pinned in truffle).\r\n\r\n## Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\n`git clone git@github.com:truffle-box/bridge-box.git`\r\n`git checkout add-message-script`\r\n`truffle migrate --network=ethereum_rinkeby --f 1 --to 1`\r\n\r\nThis will fail with:\r\n```\r\nError: Incompatible EIP155-based V 0 and chain id 1. See the second parameter of the Transaction constructor to set the chain id.\r\nat Transaction._validateV (/Users/kevinweaver/github.com/trufflesuite/truffle/node_modules/ganache-core/node_modules/ethereumjs-tx/src/transaction.ts:370:13\r\n```\r\n\r\n However if you run:\r\n`truffle migrate --network=ethereum_rinkeby --f 2 --to 2 --skip-dry-run` \r\nit succeeds.\r\n\r\n## Expected Behavior\r\n\r\nThis should succeed without skipping the dry run.\r\n\r\n## Environment\r\n\r\n* Operating System: MacOS 11.6 w/ M1 \r\n* Truffle version (`truffle version`): 5.4.15\r\n* node version (`node --version`): v14.18.0\r\n* npm version (`npm --version`): 6.14.15\r\n",
